# Superdesign — HTML design iterations only

Use when the user asks for **standalone / mockup** screens delivered as **HTML in `.superdesign/design_iterations/`**, not when editing the Next.js app.

## Output

- Single-screen HTML per iteration: `.superdesign/design_iterations/{name}_{n}.html` (unique `n`).
- Iterations on a file: `{current}_{n}.html` (e.g. `ui_1_2.html`).
- Optional companion CSS in the same folder; reference from HTML.

## Workflow (short)

1. Layout (wireframe / structure) — confirm with user if they want sign-off.
2. Theme (colors, type, spacing) — keep tokens in a local CSS file next to the HTML if needed.
3. Animation — light motion only unless asked.
4. One combined HTML (or HTML + CSS) — responsive, readable fonts (e.g. Google Fonts).

## Styling defaults

- Responsive; avoid generic “bootstrap blue” unless requested.
- Prefer Flowbite CDN + Tailwind CDN only if the task calls for that stack; otherwise plain CSS is fine.
- Do **not** paste multi-hundred-line theme blocks into rules — generate theme in the artifact file.

## App product UI

For **in-app** dashboard/pages/components, edit `app/` / `components/` like any normal Next.js work — **this rule does not apply** (see `AGENTS.md` and `docs/FEATURE_REGISTRY.md`).
